solution:
I usually call 
result.rejectValue("property", "error.object");
 to add errors to 
BindingResult
. If you want to add a global object error, you could use 
result.reject("error.object");
.

So, in your code, instead of:

ObjectError error = new ObjectError("email","An account already exists for this email.");
result.addError(error);

try with:

result.rejectValue("email", "error.user", "An account already exists for this email.");

Check the reference 
here
.

